<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A woman in her 40s has suffered a serious leg injury after being attacked by a buffalo in Sydney. </p>

<p>Paramedics were called to Campbelltown Road at Denham Court, in Sydney's southwest, at about 12.50pm on Monday.</p>

<p>It's believed the woman, in her 40s, was charged at by a buffalo.</p>

<p>She was treated by at the scene for an isolated injury to her upper leg.</p>

<p>Paramedics transported the woman to Liverpool hospital where she remains in a stable condition. </p>

<p>It's believed the woman, in her 40s, was charged at by a buffalo on Monday afternoon in Sydney's west (stock image) </p>
